This paper deals with mathematical structures and their relationships, which are common themes in several subfields of computer science. The use of category theory and algebraic structures suggests a connection to quantum computing (cs.QU) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses continuous POVMs, which are related to topology and measure theory, making subfields such as logic in computer science (cs.LO) and mathematical software (cs.MS) possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the representation of POVMs in terms of von Neumann algebras, which is related to control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY).
